 ►Cmfront::bbrick::StressCriterionClass describing a stress criterion
 ►Cmfront::bbrick::StressCriterionBaseHelper class used to build a stress criterion
 Cmfront::bbrick::Barlat2004StressCriterionThis class describes the Barlat 2004 stress criterion which is base on the following equivalent stress:

\[ \phi\left(\underline{\bf s}\right) = \sqrt[a]{ \frac{1}{4}\left( \sum_{i=0}^{3} \sum_{j=0}^{3} \left|s'_{i}-s''_{j}\right|^{a} \right) } \]

where \(s'_{i}\) and \(s''_{j}\) are the eigenvalues computed from two tensors \(\underline{\bf s}'\) and \(\underline{\bf s}''\) resulting from a linear transformation of the stress tensor:

\[ \left\{ \begin{aligned} \underline{\bf s}' &= \underline{\underline{L}}' \,\colon\,\underline{\bf s} \\ \underline{\bf s}'' &= \underline{\underline{L}}''\,\colon\,\underline{\bf s} \\ \end{aligned} \right. \]

 Cmfront::bbrick::Cazacu2001StressCriterionThis class describes the Cazacu2001 stress criterion defined by:

\[ \sigma_{\mathrm{eq}}= \sqrt{3}\,\sqrt[6]{\left(J_{2}^{O}\right)^{3} - c\,\left(J_{3}^{O}\right)^{2}} \]

where (J^{O}_{2}) and (J^{O}_{3}) are the orthotropic generalizations of the second and third invariants of the deviatoric part of the stress tensor \(\underline{\sigma}\)

 Cmfront::bbrick::Cazacu2004IsotropicStressCriterionThis class describes the Cazacu2004 orthotropic stress criterion defined by:

\[ \sigma_{\mathrm{eq}}^{C}= \sqrt[3]{\left(J_{2}^{O}\right)^{3/2} - c\,\left(J_{3}^{O}\right)} \]

where (J_{2}^{O}) and (J_{3}^{O}) are the orthotropic generalizations of the first and second invariants of the deviatoric part of the stress tensor \(\underline{\sigma}\)

 Cmfront::bbrick::Cazacu2004OrthotropicStressCriterionThis class describes the Cazacu2004Orthotropic stress criterion defined by:

\[ \sigma_{\mathrm{eq}}= \sqrt{3}\,\sqrt[6]{\left(J_{2}^{O}\right)^{3} - c\,\left(J_{3}^{O}\right)^{2}} \]

where (J^{O}_{2}) and (J^{O}_{3}) are the orthotropic generalizations of the first and second invariants of the deviatoric part of the stress tensor \(\underline{\sigma}\)

 Cmfront::bbrick::Drucker1949StressCriterionThis class describes the Drucker1949 stress criterion defined by:

\[ \sigma_{\mathrm{eq}}^{d}= \sqrt{3}\,\sqrt[6]{J_{2}^{3} - c\,J_{3}^{2}} \]

where (J_{2}) and (J_{3}) are the first and second invariants of the deviatoric part of the stress tensor \(\underline{\sigma}\)

 Cmfront::bbrick::Hill1948StressCriterionThis class describes the Hill 1948 criterion based on the Hill stress \(\sigma^{\mathrm{H}}_{\mathrm{eq}}\):

\[ \sigma^{\mathrm{H}}_{\mathrm{eq}}= H_F\left(\sigma_{11}-\sigma_{22}\right)^2+ H_G\left(\sigma_{22}-\sigma_{33}\right)^2+ H_H\left(\sigma_{33}-\sigma_{11}\right)^2+ 2H_L\sigma_{12}^{2}+ 2H_M\sigma_{13}^{2}+ 2H_N\sigma_{23}^{2} \]

 Cmfront::bbrick::Hosford1972StressCriterionThis class describes the Hosford1972 stress criterion defined by:

\[ \sigma_{\mathrm{eq}}^{H}=\sqrt[a]{\frac{1}{2}\left( \left|\sigma_{1}-\sigma_{2}\right|^{a}+ \left|\sigma_{1}-\sigma_{3}\right|^{a}+ \left|\sigma_{2}-\sigma_{3}\right|^{a}\right)} \]

where \(\sigma_{1}\), \(\sigma_{2}\) and \(\sigma_{3}\) are the eigenvalues of the stress tensor \(\underline{\sigma}\)

 Cmfront::bbrick::MisesStressCriterionThis class describes the von Mises criterion defined by:

\[ \sigma_{\mathrm{eq}} = \sqrt{\frac{3}{2}\,\underline{s}\,\colon\,\underline{s}} = \sqrt{3\,J_{2}} \]

where:

 Ctfel::math::TinyNewtonRaphson< N, T, F >Implements the Newton-Raphson algorithm when the size N of the problem is known at compile-time. One wish to solve the problem:

\[\vec{f}\left(\vec{x}\right)=\vec{0}\]

where \(\displaystyle\vec{f}:R^{N}\rightarrow R^{N}\). if \(\displaystyle\vec{x}^{n}\) is an estimation of the solution, \(\displaystyle\vec{x}^{n+1}\) will be given by:

\[\displaystyle\vec{x}^{n+1}=\vec{x}^{n}-J^{-1}\vec{f}\left(\vec{x}^{n}\right)\]

where \( J \) is the jacobien matrix of \( f \) at \(\left(\displaystyle\vec{x}^{n}\right)\) defined by \( J_{ij} = \displaystyle\frac{\displaystyle\partial f_{i}}{\displaystyle\partial x_{j}}\)

 Ctfel::math::TinyNewtonRaphson< 1u, T, F >
